    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="1054"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1054">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/387.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-14T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You will request Mexican Government to grant permission for entry into Mexico 150
                    rifles via Nuevo Laredo, and to telegraph immediately appropriate instructions
                    to officials concerned. Was it possible to secure from Vera Cruz the 50,000
                    rounds ammunition desired?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
